<subSubSection box="[199,1171,151,178]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,1171,151,178]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition taken from the 
<typeStatus box="[1020,1070,152,178]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos, 2007" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" box="[444,644,192,217]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[444,644,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Architis colombo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[651,744,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[651,744,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differ from those of other species of the genus by the anteriorly directed DTP and the large, ventrally projected prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1315,1423,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
). The females resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos, 2007" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" box="[426,608,272,297]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fritzmuelleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[426,608,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. fritzmuelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[618,715,271,297]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[618,715,271,297]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the anteriorly positioned copulatory openings and wide, strongly sclerotised CD. They can be distinguished by the small, posteriorly rounded median field, the anterior sclerotised hoods over the lateral lobes of the epigynum and by the absence of enlarged copulatory atria in the internal genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[407,548,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 14E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
