<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,344,431,457]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,431,457]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,769,471,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,471,497]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male</emphasis>
(
<materialsCitation box="[277,769,472,498]" country="Brazil" location="Colombo" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
based on 
<typeStatus box="[390,492,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B32614484F292C6F98541C99174464:8EC5C1D94849292C6D3B52FE9EB740AC" box="[564,676,472,498]" country="Brazil" name="Colombo" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Colombo</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[688,761,472,498]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Carapace brown, with a median and two lateral pale brown stripes from a posterior pale brown area to the ocular area (
<figureCitation box="[301,412,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Anterior eye row procurved, median eyes slightly larger than lateral eyes. Posterior eyes of similar size, approximately 1.5 times the diameter of anterior median eyes. Clypeus brown, chelicerae pale brown with a median dark spot anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[755,868,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites brown, sternum creamcoloured. Pedipalpi cream-coloured, with an apical brown ring on femur. Cymbium reddish-brown. Legs pale brown, with four dark rings on femora and scattered dark spots on other segments. Opisthosoma brown with a median and two lateral pale brown stripes from middle to anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1187,752,778]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma sides brown with a median pale brown spot. Venter dark brown, pale at the margins and the epigastric plate. Spinnerets pale brown, darker on ectal sides. Total length 2.9; carapace 1.3 long, 1.4 wide. Tibia I length 1.8, II 1.7, III 1.0, IV 1.4. Opisthosoma 1.5 long, 1.1 wide. VTA rounded, projected dorsally to vRTA (
<figureCitation box="[1312,1422,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
); vRTA projected ventrally, with a small ventral knob (
<figureCitation box="[768,910,912,938]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C, D</figureCitation>
); dRTA small, shorter than vRTA (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1423,912,938]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
